question: A janitor has to clean a hospital with 120 rooms. They have 5 days to get it done. It takes them 10 minutes per room. If they work 6 hours each day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning rooms?
answer:
They have to clean 24 rooms a day because 120 / 5 = <<120/5=24>>24
They spend 240 minutes cleaning per day because 24*10 = <<24*10=240>>240
They spend 4 hours a day because 240 / 60 = <<240/60=4>>4
They spend 2/3 of their day cleaning rooms because 4 / 6 = <<4/6=0.6666666666666666>>0.6666666666666666
They spend 66% of their day cleaning rooms because 0.6666666666666666*100 = <<0.6666666666666666*100=66>>66
#### 66
